text: Elling is a village with a population of 1,178 (1 January 2020)BY3: Population 1st January, by urban areas The Mobile Statbank from Statistics Denmark in the Vendsyssel region, North Jutland, Denmark, located in Elling Parish outside of Frederikshavn. 300px Nearby is Elling Å, a stream whose estuary hosts nearly extinct marsh fritillary butterflies. Its 13th-century church is especially notable. In 1938, a naturally mummified human body was found in a bog near Elling, dubbed Elling Woman. == Notable people == * Connie Nielsen (born 1965 in Frederikshavn) actress, was brought up in the town * Lotte Kiærskou (born 1975 in Frederikshavn) team handball player, won two team gold medals in the 2000 and 2004 Summer Olympics; she grew up in the town. ==References== Category:Villages in Denmark Category:Frederikshavn Municipality
title: Elling, Denmark
